         <entryFree xml:id="k000293" type="architectural feature">
            <term xml:id="term-k000293-1" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin-nt">chengchuanchuan</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000293-2" xml:lang="zh-Hant">承椽串</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000293-3" xml:lang="zh-Hans">承椽串</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000293-4" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin">chéngchuánchuàn</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000293-5" xml:lang="zh-latn-wadegile">ch`eng-ch`uan-ch`uan</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000293-6" xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000293-1" >rafter bearer</term>
            <idno type="URI">https://architecturasinica.org/keyword/k000293</idno>
            <note type="Note">
               <p>under construction</p>
               <p xml:lan="en">Chengchuan chuan 承椽串 is a type of <term ref="/keyword/k000289">chuan</term> 串. As a structural component, it first appeared in the <term ref="/keyword/k000074">Song</term> dynasty Yingzao fashi ( Li Jie 2009, 19.3a), but it is mentioned 
                  only in the section on gongxian 功限 (work units), where it is stated that its dimensions are the same as those of a you'e 由额. It is 27 fen in width and 18 fen in thickness.</p>
               <p xml:lan="en">Chen Mingda believes that the chengchuanchuan, also called chengchuan fang (承椽方, "purlin-supporting squared beam"), is a component used between the main hall columns 
                  to support fujie 副階 (pentice) rafters . According to Chen, both the size and position of this element are identical to those of the you’e (陈明达,1993, 图版 28). </p> 
               <p xml:lan="en">It is highly likely that chengchuanchuan was a scribal or authorial error for chengchuanfang. First, unlike chengchuanfang, which is clearly defined in the damuzuo (large woodwork) 
                  section of Yingzao Fashi, chengchuanchuan appears only once in a footnote within the gongxian section, and is listed alongside the squared beams framing the upper part of a wall panel (zhaobifang 照壁方), 
                  suggesting a lack of importance. Second, Chen Mingda's own interpretation of its relationship with the you’e is problematic because it gives two different names to structural components that share the 
                  same position and dimensions.</p>
               <p xml:lang="zh-Hant">承椽串是串的一種，作為建築構件名稱最早出現在宋《營造法式》（李誡2009，19.3a）但仅在“功限”的部分被提起，称其尺寸同由额（廣27分，厚18分）。陳明達認為承椽串既承椽方，是在殿身柱間承托副階椽子的構件，
                  與由額的尺寸與位置都相同。（《營造法式大木作制度研究》圖版二十八）</p>
               <p xml:lang="zh-Hant">承椽串极有可能是营造法式撰写者对”承椽方“的笔误。首先，不似承椽方在大木作部分有清楚的定义，承椽串仅在功限章节的注释里被提及一次，并且与照壁方并列。其次，陈明达关于其与由额关系的描述，也使得承椽串的
                  存在更加不符合逻辑。两个相同位置相同尺寸的构件不应当有两个名字。</p>
            </note>
